To run Movian from source, first configure


   ./configure --pepper=/PATH/TO/PEPPER_xx

   make

Then in build.nacl/stage

   python -m SimpleHTTPServer

Then start Chrome from commandline to allows NaCl from any websites and
also allow full socket access. (The latter can only be done from command line)

On OS/X:

   /Applications/Google\ Chrome.app/Contents/MacOS/Google\ Chrome --allow-nacl-socket-api=localhost  --enable-logging=stderr --enable-nacl http://localhost:8000/index.html

Go fullscreen with F11

For more key bindings see
 https://movian.tv/projects/showtime/wiki/Key_mappings

To debug, add these flags to chrome:

   --enable-nacl-debug --no-sandbox --disable-hang-monitor

And start gdb like:

 pepper_xx/toolchain/linux_arm_glibc/bin/i686-nacl-gdb -x gdb-script.txt
